==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gabbro
<hw>Gab"bro</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.]</ety>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A name originally given by the Italians to a
kind of serpentine, later to the rock called
<altname>euphotide</altname>, and now generally used for a coarsely
crystalline, igneous rock consisting of lamellar pyroxene (diallage) and
labradorite, with sometimes chrysolite (olivine gabbro).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gabel</ent>⟦br⟧
